# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHITELISTING - Files to ALWAYS COMMIT (override above patterns)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Do commit these important files:
!.gitignore
!.env.example
!requirements.txt
!manage.py
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!.github/

# Documentation should be committed
!docs/
!docs/**/*.md

# Templates should be committed
!templates/
!templates/**/*.html

# Static files source should be committed
!static/css/
!static/css/**/*.css

# Do commit clean migrations
!/*/migrations/
!/*/migrations/__init__.py
!/*/migrations/*.py

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# COMMENTS & NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# This .gitignore is comprehensive and prioritizes:
# 1. Security: API keys, credentials, tokens
# 2. Privacy: Resume files, candidate profiles, PII
# 3. Cleanliness: Build artifacts, logs, temp files
# 4. Portability: Virtual environments
#
# IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
# • Never commit .env files (use .env.example as template)
# • Never commit resume PDFs or profile JSONs
# • Never commit database files with real data
# • Always verify before committing with: git status
# • Use: git diff --cached (to review staged changes)
# • Use: git add -p (for interactive staging)
#
# If you accidentally commit sensitive files:
# git rm --cached <file>
# git commit --amend
# git push origin <branch> --force-with-lease  (use carefully!)

